Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{2} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Put the sweet potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pour the @water{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

In the meantime, trim the @cucumber{1/2}, then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @rice vinegar{15%ml} and @sugar{1}(for pickling). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then add the cucumber.

Mix together well, then set aside to pickle.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @mayonnaise{3%tbsp}, @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g} and @water{1%tbsp}(for the mayo). Mix together, then set aside your sesame mayo.

Put the @gochujang paste{50%g} in another small bowl and mix in the @honey{15%ml} and @water{2%tbsp}(for the sauce). Set aside your sticky gochujang sauce.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

When the sweet potato has ~{5%minutes} left, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @baby spinach{100%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}, reducing the heat slightly if needed.

Once wilted, stir in the @ketjap manis{25%ml}. Cook for ~{1%minute}, then remove from the heat.

Once roasted, remove the sweet potato from the oven and stir through the sticky gochujang sauce.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the gochujang roasted sweet potatoes, spinach and cucumber pickle in separate sections. Spoon over the pickling liquid and drizzle with the sesame mayo to finish.

Enjoy!